  <AbilityDef ParentName="WVC_XenotypesAndGenes_AbilitySpawnThing_Base">
	<defName>WVC_AbilitySpawn_ResurgentTree</defName>
	<label>spawn resurgent spore</label>
	<description>Spawn a resurgent spore. A resurgent spore can be used to plant a resurgent tree. The resurgent tree slowly pollutes the soil around it and raises walking corpses.</description>
	<iconPath>WVC/UI/Genes/Gene_ResurgentTree_v0</iconPath>
	<comps>
	  <li Class="WVC_XenotypesAndGenes.CompProperties_AbilityHideIfPawnMultiSelected"/>
	  <!-- <li Class="WVC_XenotypesAndGenes.CompProperties_AbilitySpawnOnCell"> -->
		<!-- <thingDef>WVC_Plant_TreeResurgent</thingDef> -->
		<!-- <allowOnNonSoil>false</allowOnNonSoil> -->
	  <!-- </li> -->
	  <li Class="WVC_XenotypesAndGenes.CompProperties_AbilitySpawn">
		<thingDef>WVC_ResurgentSeed</thingDef>
	  </li>
	  <li Class="WVC_XenotypesAndGenes.CompProperties_AbilityResurgentCost">
		<resurgentCost>0.66</resurgentCost>
	  </li>
	  <li Class="WVC_XenotypesAndGenes.CompProperties_AbilityGeneIsActive">
		<eachOfGenes>
		  <li>WVC_ResurgentCells</li>
		  <li>WVC_ResurgentCellsGain</li>
		  <li>WVC_ResurgentCells_AbilitySpawn_ResurgentTree</li>
		</eachOfGenes>
	  </li>
	</comps>
	<confirmationDialogText>After using the ability, the pawn will spend resurgent cells, but will receive a resurgent tree seed. The resurgent tree poisons the soil and spawns walking corpses, which can be controlled by a mechanitor with the "Sporelink" gene.\n\nDo you still need a resurgent seed?</confirmationDialogText>
  </AbilityDef>

